article.headline: High Point 76, VMI 75
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Landon Quick made a layup with one second remaining Wednesday night to cap a 16-5 run that lifted High Point to a 76-75 victory against VMI. The Panthers (17-10, 10-6 Big South Conference) erased a 10-point deficit in the last 3:11, pulling to within one on Jorsua Chambers' layup with 20 seconds remaining. After fouling to stop the clock, Matt Coward missed two free throws for the Keydets (6-10, 4-11) with nine seconds remaining, setting the stage for Quick's winner. Radee Skipworth had 20 points and 13 rebounds to lead VMI, including a layup to cap an 8-0 spurt that gave the Keydets a 62-53 lead with 8:01 remaining. Danny Gathings scored 20 of his 26 points in the first half for the Panthers, who clinched the number two seed in the conference tournament. Quick added 15 points, Chambers 13 and White 10. Matt Murrer scored 16 points, Fred Robinson had 13 and Coward had 11 for the Keydets, who trailed 41-38 at the half. Richard Little had 13 assists.
